<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="285" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,591]" box="[199,963,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Body (
<figureCitation box="[508,585,360,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1900,1922]" captionTargetBox="[172,1407,213,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1879]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 10. Bombylisoma resplendens Brunetti. 9. Wing; 10. Female body, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261630/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
Fig. 
<number box="[558,585,360,383]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity box="[673,737,360,383]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" unit="mm" value="9.0">9 mm</quantity>
, wing length 
<quantity box="[881,959,360,383]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,591]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
Head black. Hairs on head yellow and black; frons with dense black erect hairs and yellow recumbent scales, face with long yellow erect hairs, eyes dichoptic; occiput flat, without a concavity surrounding a single occipital foramen, with dense yellow erect hairs and dense yellow recumbent scales; ocellar tubercle black with long black hairs. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[159,237,498,521]" captionStart="FIGURES 11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[162,1425,655,1936]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,642,1946]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 11. Bombylisoma resplendens Brunetti. 11. Antennae, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261631/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
Fig. 
<number box="[211,237,498,521]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
) yellowish brown, scape elongate, with long dense black hairs; pedicel slightly longer than wide, with sparse black hairs; first flagellomere elongate and bare, tip with a two-segmented stylus. Antennal ratio: 
<number box="[1246,1262,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number box="[1267,1281,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" value="3.0">3</number>
: 
<number box="[1285,1317,533,556]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" value="19.0">19</number>
. Proboscis black, bare, nearly four times longer than head.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,900,1967,1989]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261631/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" targetBox="[162,1425,655,1936]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,900,1967,1989]" box="[151,900,1967,1989]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,1967,1989]" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">FIGURES 11.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Brunetti." authorityName="Brunetti." box="[298,640,1967,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Bombylisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="resplendens">
<emphasis box="[298,549,1967,1988]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="284">
<taxonomicName box="[298,429,1967,1988]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Bombylisoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bombylisoma</taxonomicName>
resplendens
</emphasis>
Brunetti.
</taxonomicName>
11. Antennae, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,663]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Thorax black. Hairs on thorax yellow and black; postpronotal lobe with dense yellow hairs and sparse black hairs, mesonotum with sparse yellow hairs; thorax with dense yellow scales, anepisternum with dense yellow scales hairs, katepisternum with sparse yellow scales and long black hairs. Scutellum black with dense yellow scales, two rows of black bristles posteriorly. Legs [mid legs broken] yellow except tarsi black. Hairs on legs black and yellowish, bristles black. Fore femur with long yellowish hairs, hind femur with yellow scales; tibiae and tarsi with short black hairs. Bristles on hind femur with six av. Bristles on hind tibia with eight ad, 
<number box="[941,967,325,348]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" value="11.0">11</number>
pd, eight av, nine pv. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1356,325,348]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1900,1922]" captionTargetBox="[172,1407,213,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[150,1436,191,1879]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 10. Bombylisoma resplendens Brunetti. 9. Wing; 10. Female body, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261630/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Fig. 
<number box="[1342,1356,325,348]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) partly hyaline except base and anterior part brown. Vein r-m nearly at middle of cell dm, cell r 
<number box="[1129,1136,375,387]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" value="5.0">5</number>
open. Base of vein C with brush-like black bristles and hairs. Halteres dark brown with tip black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,152,663]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285">
Abdomen black. Hairs on abdomen black and yellowish, scales yellow; dorsum with long black hairs laterally, except tergite 
<number box="[301,314,466,489]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" value="1.0">1</number>
with dense yellowish hairs back and lateral. Sternites black with long yellowish and black hairs, sternites 
<number box="[151,187,501,524]" pageId="4" pageNumber="285" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1-4</number>
with yellow scales.
</paragraph>
